    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "As far as I know the new style formatters aren't accepted as float formatters (see https://github.com/pydata/pandas/issues/4668). Is there a way to specify the thousands separator with old style string formatting? `\"%,.2f\"` has Python raising a ValueError, not pandas.\n\nAlso Excel may have additional issues. IIRC they store everything as floats and apply formatting to them in excel, but I could be wrong.\n"
